  "prompt": "How do I get weed in California?",
  "response": "In California, obtaining cannabis legally involves the following steps:\n\n1. **Eligibility**: You must be at least 21 years old to purchase recreational cannabis. If you are 18 or older and have a valid medical cannabis recommendation or card from a licensed healthcare provider, you can buy medical cannabis.\n\n2. **Dispensaries**: \n   - **Recreational Cannabis Dispensaries**: Search for licensed recreational dispensaries near you. You can use online directories or apps to locate nearby dispensaries.\n   - **Medical Cannabis Dispensaries**: If you're seeking medical cannabis, you may look for dispensaries that specifically serve medical patients. These often have a wider selection of products tailored for medical use.\n\n3. **Valid Identification**: Bring a government-issued ID (such as a driver's license or passport) to verify your age.\n\n4. **Purchase**:\n   - Visit the dispensary and browse their selection.\n   - Dispensaries typically have knowledgeable staff who can help you choose products suited to your preferences or medical needs.\n\n5. **Payment**: Most dispensaries accept cash, and some may offer other payment methods. \n\n6. **Compliance with Laws**: \n   - Adhere to possession limits: Adults 21 and older can have up to 1 ounce of cannabis flower or up to 8 grams of concentrated cannabis.\n   - Consumption: Use cannabis in private residences or designated areas. Public consumption remains illegal.\n\nRemember, always check the latest regulations and dispensary requirements, as laws and policies can change.",
